The '''Abortion Support Network''' is a [[UK]] based charity which provides financial assistance, accommodation and consultation to women from the [[Republic of Ireland]] and [[Northern Ireland]] who are seeking an abortion in the UK.

The charity was founded in 2009 by Mara Clarke.<ref name="cosmo">{{cite web|title=How This Woman Helps Hundreds of Pregnant Women in Ireland Access Safe, Legal Abortions|url=http://www.cosmopolitan.com/politics/a40652/mara-clarke-abortion-support-network-ireland/|website=Cosmopolitan|accessdate=15 December 2016|date=18 May 2015}}</ref> and continues the work of the (now defunct) [[London]] based 1980's [[Irish Women's Abortion Support Group]].

In 2015 they received widespread attention in the UK due to the popular parenting site [[Mumsnet]] using their annual charity fundraising appeal to raise money for the ASN.<ref>{{Cite newspaper|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/health/news/11666308/Mumsnet-backs-illegal-DIY-abortions.html|title =Mumsnet backs ‘illegal’ DIY abortions|date = 11 June 2015|last = Bingham|first = John|newspaper = [[The Daily Telegraph]]}}</ref>

In 2017 as part of a coalition, ASN made a submission to the [[Citizens' Assembly (Ireland)|Citizens' Assembly]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.citizensassembly.ie/en/Submissions/Eighth-Amendment-of-the-Constitution/Advocacy-Groups-and-Personal-Stories/Advocacy-Groups-May-2017.pdf|title=List of Advocacy Groups, Interest Groups, other Representative Organisations and Political Parties Submissions to the Citizens’ Assembly on the Eighth Amendment of the Constitution|last=|first=|date=12 January 2017|website=|publisher=Citizens' Assembly|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=}}</ref> That same year, ASN fund-raised and provided over £73,000 (€84,000) worth of grants for all associated expenses of obtaining an abortion, including travel. The team of volunteers fielded 1,009 phone calls (685 from Ireland) providing free advice.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.irishtimes.com/news/social-affairs/abortion-support-network-in-a-perfect-world-our-phone-would-never-ring-1.3504703|title=Abortion Support Network: ‘In a perfect world, our phone would never ring’|work=The Irish Times|access-date=2018-05-24|language=en-US}}</ref>

