{{Infobox Hospital | Name = Warren State Hospital | Org/Group = [[Pennsylvania Department of Human Services]] | Image = Warren State Hospital, 1886.png | Caption = Hospital pictured in 1886 | Logo = <!-- optional --> | Region = [[Warren, Pennsylvania|Warren]] | State = [[Pennsylvania]] | Country = US | Coordinates ={{coord|41.8792 | -79.1458 |display=inline; title}} | HealthCare = Public | Type = | Speciality = [[Psychiatric hospital]] | Standards = <!-- optional if no national standards --> | Beds = | Founded = 1880 | Closed = <!-- optional --> | Website = [http://dhs.pa.gov/citizens/statehospitals/warrenstatehospital/index.htm Warren State Hospital] }}
'''Warren State Hospital''' is a public psychiatric hospital in [[Warren, Pennsylvania]], established in 1880. The original hospital was designed by [[John McArthur, Jr.]] and constructed under the [[Kirkbride Plan]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.kirkbridebuildings.com/blog/warren-state-hospital-information|work=Kirkbride Buildings|title=Warren State Hospital|date=January 14, 2008|accessdate=May 10, 2017}}</ref> Its population peaked at 2,562 residents in 1947. As of 2017, the hospital is still active.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dhs.pa.gov/citizens/statehospitals/warrenstatehospital/|work=Department of Human Services: Pennsylvania|title=Warren State Hospital|accessdate=May 10, 2017}}</ref>
Famous residents included [[Nictzin Dyalhis]] and [[Joe_Root_(Pennsylvania)|Joe Root]]. Some famous staff included [[Penny Colman]] and [[Philipp Schwartz]].
